China [ Summary ] Interleukin - 2 receptor antagonist ( IL - 2Ra ,	O O O O O O O O O O O O O O
ie ,	O O
basiliximab and daclizumab ) ,	O O O O O
a new antibody agent ,	O O O O O
is widely employed in lowering the risk of acute rejection after organ transplantation ,	O O O O O O O O O O O O O O
but it meanwhile causes increasing concerns on the effect it exerts on glucose metabolism in transplant recipients ,	O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O
and so far the exact effect still remains controversial . New onset diabetes after transplantation ( NODAT ) is one of the most influential metabolic complications affecting graft survival and patients 忆 long - term outcomes . Some of the current researches indicate that IL - 2Ra may improve glucose metabolism in the transplant recipients ,	O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O
some show just the opposite ,	O O O O O O
yet others show no effects . Hence further investigations focusing this aspect are needed . [ Key words ] Interleukin - 2 receptor ;	O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O
